<h4 class="subsubsection"> 4.18.4.2 Embedding in a c++ application </h4>

<p>You can access Python from a C++ program by loading the <tt>&lsquo;cspython&rsquo;</tt>
Crystal Space plugin module and interacting with it via the <small>SCF</small>
<samp>&lsquo;iScript&rsquo;</samp> interface (see section <a href="iScript-Interface.html#0">The iScript Interface</a>).
</p>
<p>The <tt>&lsquo;pysimp&rsquo;</tt> example program (<tt>&lsquo;CS/apps/pysimp&rsquo;</tt>) illustrates how to do so. In addition to loading the <tt>&lsquo;cspython&rsquo;</tt> plugin, it loads and executes Python code from a sample script (which resides along with the other Python examples).
</p>
